  "description": [
    "COUNTRYBYCOUNTRY SURVEY Problems Eisenhower Will Encounter in Far East By EARL H VOSS Star Staff Writer President Eisenhowers tour of the Far East like his other official visits is billed as a purely cere monial nonnegotiating journey But the many hours scheduled for private talks with the chiefs of state and other dignitaries along the way could hardly be filled ex clusively with small talk What are the major problems which are likely to come up if not in a specific negotiating sense then in a general discus sion Here are short sketches of the principal topics of which Mr Ei senhower is likely to hear Japan The Lower House of the Jap anese Diet last month passed the JapaneseAmerican security treaty and the Upper House is expected to approve it or allow it to take effect by the time President Ei senhower arrives But militant opposition from the Socialist mi nority and leftist student groups has openly threatened to embar rass the government of Prime Minister Nobusuke Kishi by dem onstrating against the American President when he goes to Tokyo Socialists in the Diet are threat ening to resign in a further effort to embarrass the Kishi cabinet The"
